description: TEHRAN – Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian has sent a message to the Lebanese people and government offering them condolences over the explosion of electronic devices in the country at the hands of the Zionist Israeli regime which has left more than 30 people including children dead and injured nearly 4000 others.
title: Iranian president: “We sympathize with Lebanon”

description: TEHRAN - Major General Hossein Salami, the chief commander of Iran’s Islamic Revolution Guard Corps (IRGC), has told Lebanon’s Hezbollah leader Sayyed Hassan Nasrallah that Israel will face “a crushing response from the axis of resistance” after the pager and radio attacks.
title: Israel will face ‘crushing response’: IRGC commander tells Hezbollah chief

description: TEHRAN - Iran sealed their spot in the Round of 16 in style after defeating Guatemala 9-4 in their FIFA Futsal World Cup Uzbekistan 2024 Group F tie at the Bukhara Universal Sports Complex on Thursday.
title: Iran defeat Guatemala in 2024 Futsal World Cup

description: TEHRAN - In a high-profile speech on Thursday afternoon, Hezbollah Secretary General Sayyed Hassan Nasrallah said the Israeli regime intended to kill thousands of Lebanese people within minutes by exploding pagers  and walkie talkies on Tuesday and Wednesday.
title: Hezbollah chief:  Israel crosses red lines, its terrorist acts are declaration of war

description: Saudi Arabia will not normalize relations with Israel without the establishment of a Palestinian state with East Jerusalem as its capital, Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman said on Wednesday.
title: Saudi crown prince says no normalization with Israel without Palestinian statehood

description: TEHRAN – IRGC Commander Major General Hossein Salami visited the Iranian ambassador to Lebanon in a hospital in Tehran on Thursday.
title: IRGC chief visits Iranian ambassador, injured Lebanese in hospital

description: TEHRAN - Iran national football team moved up one spot to 19th in FIFA World Ranking released on Thursday.
title: Iran move up in FIFA World Rankings

description: TEHRAN – Former Iran U23 football team head coach Mehdi Mahdavikia took charge of Emirati club Al Jazira Al Hamra
title: Mahdavikia appointed Al Jazira Al Hamra head coach

description: The Lebanese army has said in a statement that “specialised army units are detonating pagers and suspicious communication devices in various regions,” the state-run news agency NNA has reported.
title: Lebanese army detonating ‘suspicious’ communication devices

description: Japan’s Icom Inc., whose brand appears on walkie-talkies that exploded in Lebanon, said it halted production a decade ago of the model allegedly used in the attacks and is still investigating the situation, the Japan Times reported on Thursday.
title: Walkie-talkies in Lebanon blasts were discontinued a decade ago: Japan

description: TEHRAN - Iran tells the United Nations that it reserves the right to respond to the recent act of sabotage and terrorism by the rogue Israeli regime in Lebanon, after Tehran’s ambassador was injured in one of the explosions in Beirut.
title: Iran tells UN it will respond to Israeli attack on ambassador in Beirut

description: The Hezbollah resistance movement has targeted an Israeli military site in the northeastern part of the occupied Palestinian territories, leaving casualties among the occupation forces.
title: Hezbollah hits Israeli military site, kills and injures 15 troops

description: TEHRAN - President Vladimir Putin has approved of a proposal by the Russian foreign ministry for signing of a strategic partnership agreement with Iran.
title: Putin endorses proposal for signing strategic partnership with Iran

description: TEHRAN - Three first half goals saw Tractor of Iran cruise to a 3-0 win over Qatar’s Al Wakrah on Wednesday in the teams’ Group A opener in the AFC Champions League Two 2024/25 at Al Wakra Stadium.
title: Tractor beat Al Wakrah in AFC Champions League Two
